3.30	Goa_literature	Goan literature	Professor Peter Nazareth points out that that Goans have written in thirteen languages, of which the chief are Konkani, Marathi, English and Portuguese. The first of these, is the mother tongue, being written in four different scripts. Nazareth is editor of an anthology of Goan writing, Professor of English and African-American World Studies and adviser to the International Writing Program at the University of Iowa. He writes:	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/bf/India_Goa_goabooks.jpg
